      <p> 
         This is a delicious, creamy, vegan coffee drink that's easy to prepare, but feels more special.
      </p>


  <title>Recipe</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:400,700|Playfair+Display:400,700" rel="stylesheet">  
</html>
<body>
  <div class="recipe">
    <div class="recipe--column">
      <div class="label">Recipe</div>
      <h2 class="title">Vegan Cold Coffee</h2>

      <img class="recipe--img" src="https://place-hold.it/400x500" />

      <section class="section">
        <div class="hint">Ready in <strong>10 minutes</strong></div>
        <div class="hint">Serves <strong>2 people</strong></div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Tips</h3>
        <div>
          I like a blend of almond milk creamer and oat milk in this drink. I haven't tried it hot, but it would probably be good.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="recipe--column">
      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>4 tablespoons sugar</li>
          <li>4 tablespoons instant coffee</li>
          <li>1/4 cup water</li>
          <li>3 cups milk of choice</li>
           <li>1/4 teaspoon vanilla</li>

        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Preparation</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Make the coffee "cream."</strong> Heat water and add in sugar and instant coffee. Stir to dissolve.
          </li>
          <li>
            Whisk this mixture (ideally using a hand mixer), until you get soft peaks and it becomes a caramel color.
          </li>
          <li>
            Pour your vegan milk of choice into a glass (ice optional). Mix in vanilla.
          </li>
          <li>
            Top with the coffee "cream." Serve with a (reusable) straw- the drink will get a stronger coffee flavor as you mix it.
          </li>

        </ol>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>


</body>
